1
00:00:01,234 --> 00:00:04,236
♪♪

2
00:00:04,407 --> 00:00:07,098
I still can't believe you're
letting me stay here.

3
00:00:07,338 --> 00:00:08,349
As your pupil.

4
00:00:08,385 --> 00:00:11,600
Shining Armor's a
father! I'm an aunt!

5
00:00:11,709 --> 00:00:13,941
Your first friendship
lesson is going to be...

6
00:00:14,130 --> 00:00:15,825
reuniting with Sunburst!

7
00:00:16,010 --> 00:00:18,850
And yes, that's me. Yep.
Ha ha. Important wizard.

8
00:00:19,301 --> 00:00:21,200
The baby is an alicorn!?

9
00:00:21,330 --> 00:00:23,054
So, she could be a
super strong flyer

10
00:00:23,098 --> 00:00:25,047
and have crazy baby magic.

11
00:00:25,090 --> 00:00:26,421
[shattering glass]

12
00:00:26,610 --> 00:00:29,498
Without the Heart, the Crystal
Empire is about to be buried

13
00:00:29,527 --> 00:00:31,403
under a mountain
of ice and snow!

14
00:00:31,469 --> 00:00:34,363
<i> ♪ [dramatic music] ♪</i>

15
00:00:38,539 --> 00:00:40,506
Hearing impaired subtitles
by YayPonies
Eat all muffins!
http://yayponies.eu/

16
00:01:12,240 --> 00:01:15,258
Rarity: So, not only
can we not take part

17
00:01:15,389 --> 00:01:17,272
in a fabulous,
ancient ceremony,

18
00:01:17,490 --> 00:01:20,189
but we're also about
to be frozen solid!

19
00:01:20,567 --> 00:01:22,741
Without the Crystal Heart's
magical protection,

20
00:01:23,032 --> 00:01:25,970
the entire city is about to
become a winter wasteland.

21
00:01:26,174 --> 00:01:27,847
But what about
when King Sombra

22
00:01:27,905 --> 00:01:28,712
ruled the
Crystal Empire

23
00:01:28,734 --> 00:01:30,094
and the Crystal
Heart was missing?

24
00:01:30,407 --> 00:01:32,240
The city wasn't
covered in snow then.

25
00:01:32,756 --> 00:01:35,069
The Heart wasn't missing.
It was still in the Castle.

26
00:01:35,309 --> 00:01:36,880
King Sombra had
just hidden it.

27
00:01:37,250 --> 00:01:39,301
I'm afraid Twilight
is correct.

28
00:01:39,469 --> 00:01:41,650
And the storm clouds
are already forming.

29
00:01:41,956 --> 00:01:43,185
[thunderclap]

30
00:01:43,270 --> 00:01:46,065
I can totally fly up there
and bust those puppies.

31
00:01:46,218 --> 00:01:47,381
No problem.

32
00:01:48,385 --> 00:01:50,181
Celestia: I wouldn't
advise it, Rainbow Dash.

33
00:01:50,414 --> 00:01:52,800
Those storm clouds are not
like the ones you know.

34
00:01:53,018 --> 00:01:55,381
This far north, the weather
has a will of its own

35
00:01:55,650 --> 00:01:57,498
and now it will
only grow stronger,

36
00:01:57,658 --> 00:01:59,316
enveloping everything
in its path.

37
00:01:59,621 --> 00:02:01,534
Including the
Crystal Empire.

38
00:02:01,643 --> 00:02:02,952
And us along with it

39
00:02:06,821 --> 00:02:08,465
There's gotta be something.

40
00:02:10,523 --> 00:02:13,040
I know Princess Twilight
is keen on the two of us

41
00:02:13,061 --> 00:02:16,123
rekindling our friendship,
but it's been so long.

42
00:02:16,378 --> 00:02:18,610
I don't see how anything on
that list is going to help.

43
00:02:19,018 --> 00:02:21,476
I know, right? It's not
like there's some spell

44
00:02:21,498 --> 00:02:24,261
that would magically compel us
to pick up where we left off.

45
00:02:24,661 --> 00:02:26,370
Oh, actually, there's several.

46
00:02:27,214 --> 00:02:29,927
Mistmane's Material Amity,
Rockhoof's Rapport,

47
00:02:30,109 --> 00:02:32,160
Flashprance's Fellowship...

48
00:02:33,716 --> 00:02:35,192
But I get the
feeling the Princess

49
00:02:35,214 --> 00:02:36,538
isn't looking for a spell.

50
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:38,341
Definitely not.

51
00:02:38,545 --> 00:02:39,272
Spike: Got it!

52
00:02:39,556 --> 00:02:42,036
"...and if all else
fails, ask them to share

53
00:02:42,080 --> 00:02:44,203
an embarrassing moment
from their past,

54
00:02:44,385 --> 00:02:46,683
maybe even something
they regret."

55
00:02:48,443 --> 00:02:50,596
Uh, I don't see how
that would help.

56
00:02:50,804 --> 00:02:54,339
Uh, yeah. We should just
get out of your mane.

57
00:02:54,494 --> 00:02:57,476
It's pretty obvious this isn't
going how Twilight hoped

58
00:02:57,563 --> 00:03:01,083
and I'm sure you have plenty
of important work to do.

59
00:03:01,941 --> 00:03:07,280
What? Oh. Right. Yes. [laugh]
No rest for the wizardly.

60
00:03:07,854 --> 00:03:08,749
Come on, Spike.

61
00:03:08,894 --> 00:03:09,847
[sigh]

62
00:03:09,912 --> 00:03:10,450
[door closes]

63
00:03:11,018 --> 00:03:14,596
<i> ♪ [dramatic music] ♪</i>

64
00:03:14,676 --> 00:03:16,596
[whistling wind]

65
00:03:16,865 --> 00:03:19,600
There must be a spell that can
restore the Crystal Heart.

66
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:20,872
Perhaps.

67
00:03:21,040 --> 00:03:23,141
But it isn't something
that either of us know.

68
00:03:23,629 --> 00:03:26,196
The library here at the
Castle is nearly as extensive

69
00:03:26,218 --> 00:03:27,410
as the one in Canterlot.

70
00:03:27,556 --> 00:03:29,745
There's a good chance we
can find something there.

71
00:03:29,934 --> 00:03:31,330
Can you hold off the storm?

72
00:03:31,629 --> 00:03:35,047
Yes, for a time, but even our
magic will eventually succumb

73
00:03:35,069 --> 00:03:36,712
to the power of
the Frozen North.

74
00:03:37,170 --> 00:03:39,861
We will do what we can,
but you must hurry.

75
00:03:45,098 --> 00:03:46,400
[zap]

76
00:03:53,912 --> 00:03:56,436
I don't know how long it will
take to find the right spell,

77
00:03:56,538 --> 00:03:58,152
but you should probably
tell the crowd outside

78
00:03:58,174 --> 00:03:59,367
to get somewhere warm.

79
00:03:59,570 --> 00:04:01,665
And try not to mention
the Crystal Heart.

80
00:04:01,963 --> 00:04:03,672
We don't want to start a panic.

81
00:04:03,905 --> 00:04:05,672
Yes, ma'am!
Come on, girls!

82
00:04:07,083 --> 00:04:08,421
I'm going to need
all of your help;

83
00:04:08,582 --> 00:04:10,315
the Crystal library
is enormous.

84
00:04:10,836 --> 00:04:12,101
You can count on us, Twiley!

85
00:04:14,094 --> 00:04:14,661
[pow]

86
00:04:14,814 --> 00:04:15,345
AHHHHHHH!

87
00:04:18,516 --> 00:04:19,316
Where'd she go?

88
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:26,898
[distant giggling]

89
00:04:27,469 --> 00:04:28,261
This way!

90
00:04:28,429 --> 00:04:31,270
[clattering hooves]

91
00:04:31,432 --> 00:04:34,690
Well, Spike, looks like my
biggest fears came true.

92
00:04:35,032 --> 00:04:36,938
I wouldn't be surprised
if Twilight decides

93
00:04:36,952 --> 00:04:38,829
to give up on me entirely.

94
00:04:39,941 --> 00:04:41,410
It's not your fault.

95
00:04:41,825 --> 00:04:44,480
I'm the one who said all
we needed was this list.

96
00:04:45,032 --> 00:04:46,058
[whoosh]

97
00:04:46,909 --> 00:04:50,494
It's not the list, Spike.
Or you. Or Twilight.

98
00:04:50,923 --> 00:04:53,309
I'm the one Sunburst doesn't
want to be friends with.

99
00:04:53,883 --> 00:04:56,400
I don't remember him saying
he didn't want to be friends.

100
00:04:56,640 --> 00:04:58,305
He didn't have to say it.

101
00:05:00,174 --> 00:05:02,029
Well, Twilight obviously thinks

102
00:05:02,043 --> 00:05:04,480
you're worth being
friends with and I do too.

103
00:05:05,665 --> 00:05:08,909
Aw thanks, Spike. At
least I have two friends,

104
00:05:08,923 --> 00:05:11,032
even if one of them
has dragon breath.

105
00:05:12,181 --> 00:05:12,909
[puff puff]

106
00:05:13,694 --> 00:05:17,243
Um, that's not dragon
breath. It's freezing!

107
00:05:17,716 --> 00:05:19,360
Oh. You're right!

108
00:05:19,665 --> 00:05:21,920
But I thought the Crystal
Heart was supposed to keep

109
00:05:21,949 --> 00:05:23,025
the cold weather out.

110
00:05:23,258 --> 00:05:25,854
It is, unless something's
happened! Come on!

111
00:05:26,026 --> 00:05:30,495
<i> ♪ [dramatic music] ♪</i>

112
00:05:30,727 --> 00:05:33,738
We're just saying that it
might not be the best idea

113
00:05:33,774 --> 00:05:35,258
to stay outside.

114
00:05:35,454 --> 00:05:37,440
I camped out all
night for this spot.

115
00:05:37,578 --> 00:05:39,309
I'm not about to
just give it up.

116
00:05:40,618 --> 00:05:42,734
Still, when you think about it,

117
00:05:42,829 --> 00:05:45,403
the view is just as good
a little further back,

118
00:05:45,490 --> 00:05:47,774
like inside your house.

119
00:05:47,992 --> 00:05:49,512
[murmurs]

120
00:05:49,745 --> 00:05:50,960
The Crystalling ceremony

121
00:05:50,989 --> 00:05:52,669
is one of our most
sacred traditions

122
00:05:52,821 --> 00:05:54,938
and when that foal is held
before the Crystal Heart,

123
00:05:55,134 --> 00:05:57,672
I plan to be as close to
the action as possible.

124
00:05:58,450 --> 00:05:59,745
Honestly, I don't know

125
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:01,221
if there's gonna
be a Crystalling.

126
00:06:01,570 --> 00:06:04,109
The truth is the
baby's an alicorn

127
00:06:04,145 --> 00:06:05,905
and her magic's plum crazy

128
00:06:05,927 --> 00:06:09,258
so you might not want to
be that close after all.

129
00:06:09,534 --> 00:06:13,461
A baby alicorn? Wow. I
can't wait to see that!

130
00:06:13,607 --> 00:06:16,298
Oh, those little wings
are probably so cute!

131
00:06:16,421 --> 00:06:17,803
I know, right?

132
00:06:18,007 --> 00:06:22,160
Look, I am 100% sure the
Crystalling isn't happening.

133
00:06:22,254 --> 00:06:28,334
[explosions]

134
00:06:28,603 --> 00:06:30,000
No Crystalling, huh?

135
00:06:30,269 --> 00:06:32,530
Then why are they
starting a fireworks show?

136
00:06:32,654 --> 00:06:35,309
WOO-HOO!

137
00:06:39,112 --> 00:06:40,109
Young filly!

138
00:06:40,858 --> 00:06:41,309
Whee!

139
00:06:41,367 --> 00:06:42,190
Come back here!

140
00:06:43,141 --> 00:06:44,901
Come to your Auntie Pinkie Pie!

141
00:06:45,069 --> 00:06:47,840
Bridlebuck's Boat Chants,
Hayhoof's Intonements,

142
00:06:48,523 --> 00:06:52,116
Mystic Maps and Mazes.
[groan] Anything up there?

143
00:06:52,901 --> 00:06:55,992
Not yet. I'm not even sure
how these are organized.

144
00:06:57,098 --> 00:06:58,138
[cooing] Geeeeya!

145
00:07:05,214 --> 00:07:08,800
Shining Armor, I thought you
were taking care of the baby.

146
00:07:09,032 --> 00:07:10,305
[cooing]

147
00:07:10,356 --> 00:07:11,752
I'm trying!

148
00:07:15,570 --> 00:07:17,389
Whoo hoo hoo!

149
00:07:17,498 --> 00:07:18,480
Gotcha!

150
00:07:19,054 --> 00:07:20,312
[pop pop]

151
00:07:20,843 --> 00:07:21,505
Or not.

152
00:07:22,778 --> 00:07:23,840
Whee!

153
00:07:24,007 --> 00:07:33,374
♪♪

154
00:07:34,683 --> 00:07:35,425
[crash]

155
00:07:35,505 --> 00:07:37,498
♪♪

156
00:07:38,843 --> 00:07:40,181
What is going on!

157
00:07:40,283 --> 00:07:41,905
You want the long or
the short version?

158
00:07:42,094 --> 00:07:42,901
Short?

159
00:07:43,083 --> 00:07:44,727
The baby's an alicorn and
she accidentally destroyed

160
00:07:44,749 --> 00:07:46,385
the Crystal Heart so Twilight
and Cadance are looking

161
00:07:46,407 --> 00:07:47,396
for a spell to put
it back together

162
00:07:47,418 --> 00:07:48,538
and save the Crystal Empire

163
00:07:48,552 --> 00:07:50,574
from turning into a giant
wasteland of ice and snow.

164
00:07:51,629 --> 00:07:52,189
Oh.

165
00:07:53,236 --> 00:07:54,094
[crash]

166
00:07:54,167 --> 00:07:54,967
[giggle]

167
00:07:57,774 --> 00:08:00,950
What about this? Trotter's
Tome of Reliquary?

168
00:08:03,207 --> 00:08:04,203
I think this is it!

169
00:08:04,632 --> 00:08:08,465
Spell of Relic Reconstitution!
I can't believe we found it.

170
00:08:08,785 --> 00:08:09,978
It's a good thing too.

171
00:08:10,058 --> 00:08:11,825
Without this, I don't
know what we'd do.

172
00:08:11,927 --> 00:08:14,029
[giggles]

173
00:08:14,327 --> 00:08:15,287
[crashing]

174
00:08:19,636 --> 00:08:20,130
[gasp]

175
00:08:20,276 --> 00:08:21,992
<i> ♪ [dramatic sting] ♪</i>

176
00:08:22,036 --> 00:08:22,836
Oops.

177
00:08:26,509 --> 00:08:29,403
That spell was the only thing
we found in the whole library

178
00:08:29,425 --> 00:08:31,272
that was even close
to what we needed.

179
00:08:31,803 --> 00:08:33,941
I'm so sorry,
Twilight!

180
00:08:34,436 --> 00:08:35,978
It's not your fault, Starlight.

181
00:08:36,269 --> 00:08:38,203
None of us were
expecting any of this.

182
00:08:38,523 --> 00:08:40,312
Do you think you can
remember the spell?

183
00:08:40,770 --> 00:08:42,363
I only read it through once!

184
00:08:42,589 --> 00:08:45,047
Well, if anypony can
exactly remember something

185
00:08:45,069 --> 00:08:46,930
she read for the first
time two minutes ago,

186
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:48,436
it's you, Twilight.

187
00:08:49,010 --> 00:08:51,730
I'll try, but I'm not
sure how long it'll take.

188
00:08:52,850 --> 00:08:54,196
[whistling wind]

189
00:08:54,247 --> 00:08:55,825
Is quickly an option?

190
00:08:56,341 --> 00:08:57,789
I'll help if I can.

191
00:08:57,934 --> 00:09:00,320
But we should evacuate
the city just in case.

192
00:09:00,516 --> 00:09:02,887
You need to lead everypony
to the train station

193
00:09:02,909 --> 00:09:04,385
before the tracks freeze over.

194
00:09:04,589 --> 00:09:06,610
We will. But between
you and Twilight,

195
00:09:06,843 --> 00:09:08,545
I'm sure you'll
remember the spell.

196
00:09:12,472 --> 00:09:14,669
I only hope this spell
is the one we need.

197
00:09:17,207 --> 00:09:18,843
Is there anything I can do?

198
00:09:19,061 --> 00:09:22,094
I don't think so. I'm just
sorry about your lesson.

199
00:09:22,203 --> 00:09:23,469
That doesn't matter now.

200
00:09:23,658 --> 00:09:26,210
Sunburst and I don't have
anything in common anyway.

201
00:09:26,450 --> 00:09:28,392
He's a big important wizard

202
00:09:28,618 --> 00:09:31,090
and I'm relearning everything
I ever thought I knew.

203
00:09:31,483 --> 00:09:34,167
Sunburst? I don't
recognize the name,

204
00:09:34,203 --> 00:09:36,210
but if he's an
important wizard,

205
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:37,454
you should
bring him here.

206
00:09:37,716 --> 00:09:39,818
Maybe he'll know what to
do if the spell fails.

207
00:09:40,392 --> 00:09:41,345
Of course!

208
00:09:42,916 --> 00:09:44,320
You better go with her, Spike.

209
00:09:51,003 --> 00:09:53,047
[thunderclap]

210
00:09:57,570 --> 00:10:00,196
Sunburst! Haven't
you looked outside?

211
00:10:01,534 --> 00:10:05,163
Snow? That's not right.
The Crystal Heart...

212
00:10:05,280 --> 00:10:06,894
...is gone. The baby...

213
00:10:06,945 --> 00:10:10,225
Shining Armor and Cadance's
baby. It's an alicorn.

214
00:10:11,505 --> 00:10:12,283
Really!?

215
00:10:12,494 --> 00:10:14,727
Really! And her magic
is a little berserk

216
00:10:14,770 --> 00:10:16,283
and, well, I guess she
destroyed the Heart.

217
00:10:16,458 --> 00:10:17,709
But Twilight thinks
she can fix it

218
00:10:17,738 --> 00:10:19,541
and Princess Cadance
thought you could help.

219
00:10:21,010 --> 00:10:21,694
Me?

220
00:10:22,043 --> 00:10:24,763
Of course! You're an important
wizard in the Crystal Empire.

221
00:10:24,785 --> 00:10:25,912
It just makes sense.

222
00:10:26,705 --> 00:10:27,192
Right.

223
00:10:27,505 --> 00:10:29,018
Right, right, right, right.

224
00:10:30,909 --> 00:10:33,185
You know, I'd like to
help. I-I really would.

225
00:10:33,250 --> 00:10:34,916
I-I just have so much, um...

226
00:10:35,178 --> 00:10:36,923
important wizard work
to do around here.

227
00:10:37,621 --> 00:10:38,349
Huh?

228
00:10:39,701 --> 00:10:41,680
Applejack: You can't stay here!

229
00:10:41,832 --> 00:10:44,312
Did I mention this was
a Royal Crystalling?

230
00:10:44,501 --> 00:10:46,690
When the Crystaller holds
the young one aloft,

231
00:10:46,930 --> 00:10:49,883
all of the Empire will
share their joy and light

232
00:10:50,087 --> 00:10:52,196
and the Crystal Heart
will beat stronger

233
00:10:52,218 --> 00:10:54,276
than it ever has before.

234
00:10:54,443 --> 00:10:56,450
It really is a moving ceremony.

235
00:10:57,600 --> 00:11:00,618
I really don't think
it's going to happen.

236
00:11:00,836 --> 00:11:03,280
Come on! It's freezing out here!

237
00:11:03,665 --> 00:11:05,876
Uh, this is the Crystal Empire.

238
00:11:05,970 --> 00:11:07,803
We've seen snow before.

239
00:11:08,196 --> 00:11:09,818
Not like this!

240
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:12,101
Shining Armor: We don't
have time to argue.

241
00:11:12,312 --> 00:11:14,967
Princess Cadance has decided
to evacuate the city.

242
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:16,392
[the crowd gasps]

243
00:11:16,545 --> 00:11:18,043
But the Crystalling!

244
00:11:18,327 --> 00:11:19,941
I don't know if we'll
ever have another

245
00:11:19,963 --> 00:11:21,170
Crystalling again.

246
00:11:21,447 --> 00:11:24,007
The Crystal Heart is shattered.

247
00:11:24,145 --> 00:11:26,938
[worried murmurs]

248
00:11:27,112 --> 00:11:28,596
It's not safe here!

249
00:11:29,876 --> 00:11:32,625
That's what we've been
trying to tell you!

250
00:11:33,032 --> 00:11:36,960
[galloping hooves]

251
00:11:37,178 --> 00:11:40,407
Sunburst, I know you're busy,
but did you hear what I said?

252
00:11:40,981 --> 00:11:43,360
Oh, I heard you,
but-but like I said,

253
00:11:43,381 --> 00:11:45,818
when you're an important
wizard the work just piles up.

254
00:11:45,934 --> 00:11:46,960
Sunburst!

255
00:11:48,043 --> 00:11:48,785
[sigh]

256
00:11:49,098 --> 00:11:52,043
Look, Starlight, I
want to help, I do.

257
00:11:52,443 --> 00:11:54,807
But I can't. I wish I could.

258
00:11:55,127 --> 00:11:56,334
What do you mean?

259
00:11:56,829 --> 00:11:58,356
Fixing an ancient relic?

260
00:11:58,378 --> 00:12:01,083
I-I can't even come close to
doing something like that!

261
00:12:01,425 --> 00:12:04,043
But I thought you were
an important wizard.

262
00:12:04,996 --> 00:12:06,560
Well, you were wrong! OK?

263
00:12:06,734 --> 00:12:10,283
I'm not an important wizard!
I'm not even a wizard at all!

264
00:12:10,385 --> 00:12:13,774
<i> ♪ [dramatic] ♪</i>

265
00:12:15,454 --> 00:12:18,240
[rushing wind]

266
00:12:18,312 --> 00:12:21,025
♪♪

267
00:12:21,100 --> 00:12:22,792
I know it's hard for
you to understand,

268
00:12:22,814 --> 00:12:25,381
but not all of us end
up achieving greatness!

269
00:12:25,883 --> 00:12:28,843
What? Why wouldn't
I understand that?

270
00:12:29,469 --> 00:12:32,552
Really? You're the protégé of
the Princess of Friendship.

271
00:12:32,669 --> 00:12:34,996
I don't think she picks
just anypony for that.

272
00:12:36,174 --> 00:12:38,560
Technically, she's more of
a student than a protégé.

273
00:12:40,509 --> 00:12:43,730
Whatever. I'm sorry I'm not
the big, important wizard

274
00:12:43,752 --> 00:12:44,821
you were expecting.

275
00:12:45,963 --> 00:12:48,807
Sunburst! I don't care if
you're a wizard or not.

276
00:12:48,829 --> 00:12:52,269
I'm just surprised. You always
knew so much about magic.

277
00:12:52,509 --> 00:12:54,145
I mean, look at all these books!

278
00:12:55,338 --> 00:12:58,087
Yeah, well, reading
about magic is one thing,

279
00:12:58,109 --> 00:13:00,363
but you don't know what it
was like at Magic School,

280
00:13:00,654 --> 00:13:03,738
to know so much and not
be able to do any of it!

281
00:13:06,698 --> 00:13:09,265
Well, you don't know what it
was like to be left behind!

282
00:13:09,410 --> 00:13:11,592
And then getting so bitter
that you steal the cutie marks

283
00:13:11,614 --> 00:13:13,730
from an entire village
and then get defeated

284
00:13:13,752 --> 00:13:14,974
by Twilight and her friends.

285
00:13:15,025 --> 00:13:16,705
So you travel through
time to get back at them,

286
00:13:16,727 --> 00:13:19,018
but they beat you again and
teach you about friendship,

287
00:13:19,054 --> 00:13:21,840
but you're so terrified ponies
will find out what you did

288
00:13:21,869 --> 00:13:23,760
that you can't make any friends!

289
00:13:30,530 --> 00:13:32,021
Did you really
travel through time?

290
00:13:32,970 --> 00:13:34,974
See? I told you
he'd be impressed.

291
00:13:35,745 --> 00:13:38,930
I'm sorry we lost touch.
Maybe if I had reached out,

292
00:13:39,010 --> 00:13:40,785
you could have helped
me at Magic School

293
00:13:40,836 --> 00:13:42,145
and I could have
helped you to...

294
00:13:42,389 --> 00:13:44,289
Not become totally evil?

295
00:13:46,589 --> 00:13:49,672
[sigh] Let's just say
I know what it's like

296
00:13:49,694 --> 00:13:52,618
to have something you're
not exactly proud of.

297
00:13:52,916 --> 00:13:55,432
You showed up thinking
I was some big wizard.

298
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:58,705
I'm sorry. I should
have told you the truth.

299
00:13:59,192 --> 00:14:01,920
It's fine. At least
we worked it all out.

300
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:03,941
I think Twilight
would be proud of us.

301
00:14:04,210 --> 00:14:06,385
Well, if you ever want
to tell her about it,

302
00:14:06,487 --> 00:14:08,007
we should probably leave now!

303
00:14:08,683 --> 00:14:11,127
I forgot to tell you,
they're evacuating the city!

304
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:12,960
You need to get to
the train station,

305
00:14:13,090 --> 00:14:14,414
unless you've got a spell here

306
00:14:14,436 --> 00:14:15,680
that will drive back
the Frozen North

307
00:14:15,701 --> 00:14:16,589
and fix the Crystal Heart

308
00:14:16,603 --> 00:14:17,978
so the baby can have
her Crystalling?

309
00:14:19,214 --> 00:14:22,029
The Crystalling. Of course!

310
00:14:22,167 --> 00:14:27,330
♪♪

311
00:14:27,634 --> 00:14:31,970
[zap]

312
00:14:32,072 --> 00:14:34,501
[grunts]

313
00:14:34,567 --> 00:14:36,574
Push them back, my sister!

314
00:14:38,878 --> 00:14:40,478
[whistling wind]

315
00:14:40,589 --> 00:14:46,320
♪♪

316
00:14:46,472 --> 00:14:47,556
This way!

317
00:14:47,621 --> 00:14:49,420
[shouts]

318
00:14:55,781 --> 00:14:57,178
[whoosh]

319
00:14:57,564 --> 00:14:58,897
[grunt]

320
00:15:01,643 --> 00:15:03,345
Just a little bit
further, y'all!

321
00:15:03,447 --> 00:15:04,858
The station's just ahead!

322
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,825
We have to go back!

323
00:15:12,340 --> 00:15:14,167
I know how to stop this!

324
00:15:23,054 --> 00:15:25,505
Uh, I think that's everything.

325
00:15:26,952 --> 00:15:28,094
It looks right to me,

326
00:15:28,138 --> 00:15:30,465
but there's only
one way to find out.

327
00:15:32,564 --> 00:15:37,368
[whoosh]

328
00:15:44,007 --> 00:15:45,745
[shatter]

329
00:15:46,865 --> 00:15:49,629
The spell failed. I don't
know what else to do.

330
00:15:50,080 --> 00:15:52,872
An old student of
mine believes he does.

331
00:15:57,541 --> 00:15:58,967
The baby did this!?

332
00:15:59,236 --> 00:16:00,814
I tried putting it
back together with...

333
00:16:00,909 --> 00:16:02,567
...the Spell of Relic
Reconstitution.

334
00:16:02,720 --> 00:16:03,585
That won't do it.

335
00:16:03,854 --> 00:16:05,549
The Crystal Heart's been
around for millennia.

336
00:16:05,818 --> 00:16:08,647
Restoring a relic like this is
magic way beyond one spell.

337
00:16:08,930 --> 00:16:10,705
You'd need to combine
it with something else,

338
00:16:10,814 --> 00:16:12,749
something unique to
the relic itself,

339
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:16,458
something that strengthens it
and provides it with power.

340
00:16:18,036 --> 00:16:19,280
The Crystalling!

341
00:16:19,752 --> 00:16:22,203
Combining that spell
with the light and love

342
00:16:22,247 --> 00:16:25,127
of everypony gathered for the
ceremony, together with...

343
00:16:25,716 --> 00:16:27,738
Somnambula's Weather Abjuration

344
00:16:27,752 --> 00:16:29,745
to clear away the snow and...

345
00:16:30,116 --> 00:16:32,676
A little Fledgling's
Forbearance for the parents.

346
00:16:33,390 --> 00:16:34,960
[cooing]

347
00:16:35,134 --> 00:16:37,825
That should curb the little
one's power fluctuations.

348
00:16:37,883 --> 00:16:39,680
[cooing]

349
00:16:39,890 --> 00:16:41,418
You must be Sunburst.

350
00:16:41,490 --> 00:16:43,570
Starlight said you
were a powerful wizard.

351
00:16:43,956 --> 00:16:45,265
Oh, I'm no wizard.

352
00:16:45,490 --> 00:16:46,378
Huh? What?

353
00:16:47,498 --> 00:16:49,890
But he studied magic
his whole life!

354
00:16:50,130 --> 00:16:51,272
You should see his house!

355
00:16:51,461 --> 00:16:53,629
And since no pony
has any better ideas,

356
00:16:53,774 --> 00:16:55,549
what do we have to lose?

357
00:16:59,614 --> 00:17:02,203
I had planned on asking
Twilight to be our Crystaller,

358
00:17:02,363 --> 00:17:04,341
but since it seems
like she'll be busy...

359
00:17:04,724 --> 00:17:06,557
[cooing]

360
00:17:06,676 --> 00:17:07,636
I'd be honored.

361
00:17:09,090 --> 00:17:10,945
Well, what are we waiting for?

362
00:17:11,163 --> 00:17:17,381
♪♪

363
00:17:24,540 --> 00:17:25,927
[groan]

364
00:17:26,516 --> 00:17:36,050
♪♪

365
00:17:36,101 --> 00:17:46,043
♪♪

366
00:17:46,109 --> 00:17:52,356
<i> ♪ [majestic theme] ♪</i>

367
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:55,272
Citizens, may I present
the newest member

368
00:17:55,294 --> 00:17:57,127
of the Crystal Empire!

369
00:18:01,512 --> 00:18:05,680
[delighted squeals]

370
00:18:05,803 --> 00:18:07,265
She's beautiful.

371
00:18:07,469 --> 00:18:09,592
Oh! It's just so moving.

372
00:18:36,763 --> 00:18:41,750
[whoosh]

373
00:18:41,781 --> 00:18:42,872
[giggle]

374
00:18:46,283 --> 00:18:48,720
[shouts]

375
00:18:57,432 --> 00:18:59,956
Best. Crystalling. Ever!

376
00:19:03,185 --> 00:19:06,952
For a Pony who isn't great at
magic, you did pretty well.

377
00:19:07,547 --> 00:19:08,613
Celestia: Indeed.

378
00:19:08,901 --> 00:19:10,450
I'm glad to see
you've found a way

379
00:19:10,480 --> 00:19:12,770
to share your unique
gift, Sunburst.

380
00:19:13,090 --> 00:19:15,680
You may be more of a
wizard than you think.

381
00:19:20,298 --> 00:19:22,661
You would not believe
the crazy weather

382
00:19:22,683 --> 00:19:23,818
that delayed our train!

383
00:19:24,450 --> 00:19:25,476
Came out of nowhere!

384
00:19:25,796 --> 00:19:28,872
But it was all worth it to see
this peaceful little angel.

385
00:19:29,352 --> 00:19:33,105
Aww so sweet, come
to your grandmare.

386
00:19:33,236 --> 00:19:34,749
[giggle]

387
00:19:35,003 --> 00:19:37,425
Yeah. Peaceful now, anyway.

388
00:19:37,658 --> 00:19:39,898
I suppose that spell
really did the trick.

389
00:19:40,312 --> 00:19:42,858
[starting to sneeze]

390
00:19:42,952 --> 00:19:43,905
Aaaah!

391
00:19:44,421 --> 00:19:46,269
Achoo!

392
00:19:50,550 --> 00:19:52,429
We have Sunburst
to thank for that.

393
00:19:52,625 --> 00:19:55,636
I hope he takes his role
as Crystaller seriously.

394
00:19:55,912 --> 00:19:58,858
Something tells me the baby
will need a pony like him

395
00:19:59,090 --> 00:20:00,814
to look to for magical advice.

396
00:20:01,210 --> 00:20:03,330
Cadence, darling,
aren't we going to name

397
00:20:03,360 --> 00:20:04,952
the poor little dear or
are we going to spend

398
00:20:04,974 --> 00:20:07,578
the entire visit just
calling her "the baby?"

399
00:20:08,625 --> 00:20:11,730
We were thinking, Flurry Heart.

400
00:20:12,043 --> 00:20:13,890
You know, to remember
the occasion.

401
00:20:14,232 --> 00:20:17,207
Oh goodness! How
could anypony forget?

402
00:20:17,672 --> 00:20:19,018
I think it's lovely.

403
00:20:19,309 --> 00:20:19,650
[kiss]

404
00:20:19,810 --> 00:20:20,741
[laugh]

405
00:20:22,901 --> 00:20:25,010
Well, I think you're
the Crystal Empire's

406
00:20:25,098 --> 00:20:28,290
big, important wizard,
whether you like it or not.

407
00:20:28,712 --> 00:20:30,749
I don't know if I'll have
time for any wizarding.

408
00:20:30,930 --> 00:20:33,316
I'm a Crystaller now.
That's a big responsibility.

409
00:20:33,694 --> 00:20:36,341
I can't think of
anypony more qualified.

410
00:20:36,727 --> 00:20:38,610
Just promise you'll
stay in touch?

411
00:20:39,490 --> 00:20:41,760
Like I'd ever lose touch
with my oldest friend.

412
00:20:46,850 --> 00:20:48,298
What's wrong, Twilight?

413
00:20:49,214 --> 00:20:50,567
I don't know, Spike.

414
00:20:50,705 --> 00:20:53,287
I think I have a lot to
learn about being a teacher.

415
00:20:53,578 --> 00:20:56,305
What are you talking about?
Your lesson went perfectly.

416
00:20:56,530 --> 00:20:58,290
Starlight and Sunburst
got over their past

417
00:20:58,312 --> 00:20:59,505
and rekindled their friendship.

418
00:20:59,665 --> 00:21:00,850
No thanks to me.

419
00:21:01,069 --> 00:21:03,709
I know a lot happened; I
just wish I could have given

420
00:21:03,723 --> 00:21:06,029
my pupil the attention
she deserves.

421
00:21:07,789 --> 00:21:11,076
Well, I know she needed to
be put on the right path,

422
00:21:11,447 --> 00:21:13,389
but giving her the space
to make her own decisions

423
00:21:13,410 --> 00:21:14,334
worked pretty well.

424
00:21:14,690 --> 00:21:16,581
Isn't that how
Celestia taught you?

425
00:21:18,036 --> 00:21:21,447
You know, I never thought
about it, but I guess it is.

426
00:21:21,854 --> 00:21:24,123
Maybe you're a better
teacher than you thought.

427
00:21:24,510 --> 00:21:33,949
♪♪

